<body>
    <h1>Semantic Clones (Similar Functions and Pattern Matches) - Revised F=
eature Spec</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h2 local-id=3D"bee387bfba10" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctions=
andPatternMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-1.Metadata">1. Metadata</h2>
<p local-id=3D"85af54b2ee9f"><em>(Administrative information for ownership,=
 tracking, and lifecycle management.)</em></p>
<ul local-id=3D"010f5bcd3cb4">
<li local-id=3D"d518732fc438">
<p local-id=3D"6c141ab1e7e6"><strong>Feature name:</strong> Semantic Clones=
 (Similar Functions and Pattern Matches)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e3637ba35ab4">
<p local-id=3D"e17c32dac92f"><strong>Module(s):</strong> DevQL semantic plu=
gin, ingest enrichment pipeline, query pipeline</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"80a082442031">
<p local-id=3D"986dfcf72409"><strong>Tech lead:</strong> TBD</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"fff5bbc86344">
<p local-id=3D"c49e119f07df"><strong>Status:</strong> Draft</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b92d545f496a">
<p local-id=3D"9b76c20cf417"><strong>Priority:</strong> High</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"18fd755ac371">
<p local-id=3D"8a66f9a3e028"><strong>Target release:</strong> TBD</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e348b1d9af33">
<p local-id=3D"99e7edf9cc01"><strong>Related Feature spec brief:</strong> S=
emantic clone enrichment and retrieval MVP</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1a68770a56a3">
<p local-id=3D"1e8d0d63ee30"><strong>Related Jira epic:</strong> <a class=
=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://bitloops.atlassian.net/browse/CLI-1319" =
rel=3D"nofollow">CLI-1319 - Semantic clone enrichment and retrieval MVP</a>=
</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"76e0d9742d0d">
<p local-id=3D"b535d2358ffd"><strong>Depends on:</strong> <a href=3D"https:=
//bitloops.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ADCP/pages/433946625/Artefact+Completi=
on+and+Blast+Radius" data-linked-resource-id=3D"433946625" data-linked-reso=
urce-version=3D"16" data-linked-resource-type=3D"page">Artefact completion =
and Blast radius</a>, <a href=3D"https://bitloops.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces=
/ADCP/pages/448233476/DevQL+Capability+Architecture+Core+vs+First-Party+Plu=
gins+and+Future+Third-Party+Model" data-linked-resource-id=3D"448233476" da=
ta-linked-resource-version=3D"3" data-linked-resource-type=3D"page">DevQL C=
apability Architecture: Core vs First-Party Plugins and Future Third-Party =
Model</a></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"85904735ab78">
<p local-id=3D"79b1113677ad"><strong>Reference glossary:</strong> <a href=
=3D"https://bitloops.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ADCP/pages/394952711/Glossar=
y+Ubiquitous+Language" data-linked-resource-id=3D"394952711" data-linked-re=
source-version=3D"15" data-linked-resource-type=3D"page">Glossary / Ubiquit=
ous Language</a></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b738f433092f">
<p local-id=3D"69c0d931eb04"><strong>Supersedes draft:</strong> <a href=3D"=
https://bitloops.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ADCP/pages/432504852/Semantic+Cl=
ones+Similar+Functions+and+Pattern+Matches" data-linked-resource-id=3D"4325=
04852" data-linked-resource-version=3D"23" data-linked-resource-type=3D"pag=
e">Semantic Clones (Similar Functions and Pattern Matches)</a></p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"899589805070">
<h2 local-id=3D"56acba5ebf4f" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-2.Overview">2. Overview</h2>
<p local-id=3D"9fee979321c2"><em>(High-level explanation of the feature's i=
ntent. Describe the problem, why it matters, and what success looks like. T=
his section provides context, not implementation detail.)</em></p>
<h3 local-id=3D"d41bb2b119c9" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-Problemstatement">Problem statement</h3>
<p local-id=3D"af0de774fea2">Bitloops can already reason about structural c=
ode relationships through artefact extraction and dependency edges, but it =
cannot yet answer an important higher-level question reliably:</p>
<p local-id=3D"1055314fe61a"><strong>"What local implementation is most sim=
ilar to this one, and why?"</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"27af528baf3f">Without this capability:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"7e252c533482">
<li local-id=3D"c8577a28a8ee">
<p local-id=3D"572ed419e145">developers, reviewers, and agents must scan ma=
ny files manually to find reusable local patterns</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"92d7dfcbcc49">
<p local-id=3D"863fefea350c">duplicate or near-duplicate logic is easy to m=
iss</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ed2956fe728f">
<p local-id=3D"d23e18de3659">it is hard to tell whether two similar pieces =
of code are different on purpose or because they drifted apart by mistake</=
p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f97dcf5620bd">
<p local-id=3D"48ee14fad050">context bundles sent to AI agents contain more=
 low-signal code than necessary</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"4300f0a0133d">Semantic Clones fills that gap by taking the s=
tructural outputs from <a href=3D"https://bitloops.atlassian.net/wiki/space=
s/ADCP/pages/433946625/Artefact+Completion+and+Blast+Radius" data-linked-re=
source-id=3D"433946625" data-linked-resource-version=3D"16" data-linked-res=
ource-type=3D"page">Blast Radius</a> and adding semantic summaries, embeddi=
ngs, and a combined scoring system so Bitloops can find <a href=3D"https://=
bitloops.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ADCP/pages/394952711/Glossary+Ubiquitous=
+Language" data-linked-resource-id=3D"394952711" data-linked-resource-versi=
on=3D"15" data-linked-resource-type=3D"page">clone-like neighbours</a> (sim=
ilar code) and explain the reason for each match.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"6e487a75bdfd" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-Whythismatters">Why this matters</h3>
<p local-id=3D"79d21557ac9b">This feature provides concrete product capabil=
ities, not just internal enrichment:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"61=
987c5e0ca1" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"ce36ec5bbcad">
<th data-local-id=3D"88244419b6eb" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"f228d85e367d"><strong>Capability</strong></p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"34f9fa507c6d" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"cc73976de18f"><strong>Who uses it</strong></p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"4a75dd06556f" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"6c25c664ee1a"><strong>What it enables</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"93ac0eb2e257">
<td data-local-id=3D"b62fb6d22937" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"cbb833115209">Find similar implementations by intent</p></td=
>
<td data-local-id=3D"7023628b9265" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"85e6043f3dcf">Developer, Reviewer, AI agent</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"4e9a134bb535" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"30237147343d">Reuse local patterns even when names differ</p=
></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"71c0acbe3742">
<td data-local-id=3D"560920f7289b" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a9407e2a332b">Detect exact duplicates</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"e133696a1a16" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"97b1979a33de">Developer, Reviewer</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"7942837c3ee7" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"284ba9b961f1">Identify copy-paste logic that should be conso=
lidated</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"ea109ab1bf43">
<td data-local-id=3D"17b51b34e668" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"548c77aee024">Detect shared logic candidates</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"d145a71a108a" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"45dcd202819b">Developer, Reviewer</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"63abb896b412" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"64188576db2e">Spot repeated logic that can be turned into sh=
ared helpers</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"be15abf8ff31">
<td data-local-id=3D"b26d92b67d37" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9cb01983eb39">Detect diverged implementation</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"c163e913e93a" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3f51b46ed823">Developer, Reviewer</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"7dc1f63a19da" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8151b5dca1ad">See when two related implementations have drif=
ted apart and may need review</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"4664d21834cc">
<td data-local-id=3D"43bed4ff127f" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2e1196461435">Surface weak clone candidates</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"6665c03a2784" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a1959f93472e">Developer, Reviewer</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"5efabe82a2b4" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7462f26dec79">Show nearby code worth inspecting without over=
stating confidence</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"1b794efa80c3">
<td data-local-id=3D"a0fd74731ec5" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2ce1b7fa0a64">Surface preferred local patterns</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"4c5f6048da02" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2fe3042d5b50">AI agent, Developer</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"ead3c3ca24c1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"aeef9f7478d6">Bias code generation and refactors toward stab=
le repository conventions</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"3bfb7aa8eea6">
<td data-local-id=3D"97436786350c" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"84ebaaba106e">Compress context</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"48e5e3df7155" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"75577805598f">AI agent</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"9745c8729487" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b7136da2240a">Return a small, relevant, explainable set of s=
imilar artefacts instead of scanning many files</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"f04884e3226b" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-Expectedproductimprovements">Expected product=
 improvements</h3>
<p local-id=3D"00b32067adfd">For the MVP, this feature is expected to impro=
ve the system in five specific ways:</p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"c01c4ac21c23">
<li local-id=3D"a5da145ca092">
<p local-id=3D"0647a0dcdc97"><strong>Higher-quality local reuse:</strong> B=
itloops can recommend examples from the same repo instead of suggesting gen=
eric solutions/patterns.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"de6d8c49d783">
<p local-id=3D"41647499d54a"><strong>Lower review effort:</strong> reviewer=
s can quickly see whether repeated logic is exact duplication, intentional =
variation, drift, or only a weak contextual neighbour.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1cd88fd745c7">
<p local-id=3D"f95f3a7c3ee5"><strong>Better agent context quality:</strong>=
 agents receive the most relevant similar artefacts plus simple summaries i=
nstead of lots of extra code.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ea89869677e2">
<p local-id=3D"4d8437c2cdef"><strong>Token reduction in retrieval workflows=
:</strong> the system can return a few useful matches directly, instead of =
searching through a much larger set first.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"774d3f41edda">
<p local-id=3D"610f96823aef"><strong>Clearer results:</strong> each match i=
ncludes a score and explanation, so people can understand why it was return=
ed.</p></li>
</ol>
<hr local-id=3D"33508c9e76c0">
<h2 local-id=3D"84dda20c9bcf" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-3.Scope">3. Scope</h2>
<p local-id=3D"921ba3130ee1"><em>(Precise boundaries of what will and will =
not be built in this feature. This section defines implementation limits an=
d prevents scope creep.)</em></p>
<h3 local-id=3D"c3515e0495b7" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-Inscope">In scope</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"c5629b003bc6">
<li local-id=3D"07d7d1537b8e">
<p local-id=3D"43daad9eb0d5">Same-repo, same-snapshot semantic clone retrie=
val. Means artefacts are compared from the same indexed state of the repo, =
not from different points in history.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"98b156f7be3b">
<p local-id=3D"f69333ece396">Parser-backed artefacts produced by Blast Radi=
us. Parse <strong>eligible artefacts</strong> (artefacts included in this f=
eature extracted from Blast Radius except from <code>imports</code> for now=
).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c647bd79de19">
<p local-id=3D"c1f8315ae0c4">Supported languages: <strong>TypeScript, JavaS=
cript, Rust</strong>.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"db9303aa9deb">
<p local-id=3D"6959362018db">One-line summary generation for every eligible=
 artefact.<br>
Why and design: <a href=3D"https://bitloops.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ADCP/=
pages/460521488/Semantic+Clones+Stage+1+-+Summaries+and+Retrieval+Features"=
 data-linked-resource-id=3D"460521488" data-linked-resource-version=3D"13" =
data-linked-resource-type=3D"page">Semantic Clones Stage 1 - Summaries and =
Retrieval Features</a></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0acf56fd60a1">
<p local-id=3D"ce614bf4dafc">Lexical, structural, and semantic feature gene=
ration for eligible artefacts.<br>
Why and design: <a href=3D"https://bitloops.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ADCP/=
pages/460521488/Semantic+Clones+Stage+1+-+Summaries+and+Retrieval+Features"=
 data-linked-resource-id=3D"460521488" data-linked-resource-version=3D"13" =
data-linked-resource-type=3D"page">Semantic Clones Stage 1 - Summaries and =
Retrieval Features</a></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"39c9511c4988">
<p local-id=3D"1174180630d8">Embedding generation and vector search for eli=
gible artefacts.<br>
Why and design: <a href=3D"https://bitloops.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ADCP/=
pages/460488718/Semantic+Clones+Stage+2+-+Embeddings" data-linked-resource-=
id=3D"460488718" data-linked-resource-version=3D"16" data-linked-resource-t=
ype=3D"page">Semantic Clones Stage 2 - Embeddings</a></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d28473bdaf79">
<p local-id=3D"b0b6ec1912c7">Combined ranking from above with explicit scor=
es.<br>
Why and design: <a href=3D"https://bitloops.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ADCP/=
pages/460587023/Semantic+Clones+Stage+3+-+Combined+Ranking+and+Clone+Edges"=
 data-linked-resource-id=3D"460587023" data-linked-resource-version=3D"10" =
data-linked-resource-type=3D"page">Semantic Clones Stage 3 - Combined Ranki=
ng and Clone Edges</a></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f020d6715aa7">
<p local-id=3D"477e1145ec11">Blast Radius call and dependency edge context =
is taken into account in Stage 3 scoring and explanations.<br>
Why and design: <a href=3D"https://bitloops.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ADCP/=
pages/460587023/Semantic+Clones+Stage+3+-+Combined+Ranking+and+Clone+Edges"=
 data-linked-resource-id=3D"460587023" data-linked-resource-version=3D"10" =
data-linked-resource-type=3D"page">Semantic Clones Stage 3 - Combined Ranki=
ng and Clone Edges</a></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b5c42690adfa">
<p local-id=3D"70744758f0bb">Relation kind (for exact definition check <str=
ong>4. Definitions</strong>):</p>
<ul local-id=3D"2ec43f7406ce">
<li local-id=3D"912427c2f4c8">
<p local-id=3D"ee84761e406f"><code>exact_duplicate</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7fa69719f853">
<p local-id=3D"5b69091a7d8c"><code>similar_implementation</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0819ce32394e">
<p local-id=3D"813b2d9f4c9f"><code>shared_logic_candidate</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"18f873300a6c">
<p local-id=3D"ae25d1cd093e"><code>diverged_implementation</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"366eea2d99b0">
<p local-id=3D"d9d0126dc03c"><code>weak_clone_candidate</code></p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"c3a2ba55bd81">
<p local-id=3D"6dffdf972d09">A <code>preferred_local_pattern</code> label o=
n top of ranked results.<br>
Why and design: <a href=3D"https://bitloops.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ADCP/=
pages/460587023/Semantic+Clones+Stage+3+-+Combined+Ranking+and+Clone+Edges"=
 data-linked-resource-id=3D"460587023" data-linked-resource-version=3D"10" =
data-linked-resource-type=3D"page">Semantic Clones Stage 3 - Combined Ranki=
ng and Clone Edges</a></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c4d52ea202f6">
<p local-id=3D"bc44506079b3">Incremental recomputation using input hashes a=
nd version checks, so unchanged artefacts can reuse previously generated su=
mmaries and embeddings instead of recomputing everything on every run.</p><=
/li>
<li local-id=3D"4743ea681141">
<p local-id=3D"0eea8670809c">Expose a queryable clone result that is explai=
nable enough for both human review and agent use.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"a12e20b4c549" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-Outofscope">Out of scope</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"0e56bc77ea27">
<li local-id=3D"14698f33b571">
<p local-id=3D"e8884b283d25"><code>import</code> artefacts are excluded fro=
m semantic enrichment and clone-edge generation.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c02b4e287aa9">
<p local-id=3D"12a1e355a46e">Cross-kind matches are excluded. Source and ta=
rget must have the same effective kind.<br>
e.g. We should compare artefact with <code>kind: method</code> with an equa=
l artefact kind.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9a55abdf103b">
<p local-id=3D"4e2da840aacb">Querying clone results for an older repository=
 snapshot, for example at a specific commit with <code>asOf(...)</code>, is=
 not supported by <code>clones()</code> today. It only works on the current=
 indexed repository state.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cd74a7b05c49">
<p local-id=3D"a48ad3e6b32c">Cross-repo retrieval.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d2dd18cf1606">
<p local-id=3D"20f93ba7e073">Clone detection across all programming languag=
es.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"84a189fe0179">
<p local-id=3D"e8efe26bf932">Clone detection for local variables, class fie=
lds or property declarations. Because these are not supported by Blast Radi=
us yet.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"b7b5ec4b5cf1">
<h2 local-id=3D"394e6c1d494a" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-4.Definitions">4. Definitions</h2>
<p local-id=3D"11b13d931f6e"><em>(This section resolves ambiguity in featur=
e-specific terms so the rest of the document can be precise.)</em></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"17=
8f7530664a" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"e1e61f6fd3ff">
<th data-local-id=3D"97f1005c86da" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"d638e249a418">Term</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"211b67185807" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"ec1e420ed192">Definition</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"07b205d2a022">
<td data-local-id=3D"cc5e6f278e7c" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"bdfd1b81d5de"><strong>Clone</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"0b2957f9a251" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"406e7f5933df">In this feature, a clone is a pair of eligible=
 artefacts in the same repository snapshot that are either exactly equivale=
nt or sufficiently similar in intent/shape to be useful for reuse, deduplic=
ation, or drift analysis.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"385484f69d3a">
<td data-local-id=3D"453ece080835" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8c8244191ae5"><strong>Eligible artefact</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"7d77df461011" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8e361491e734">An artefact whose kind exists in Blast Radius =
output except from <code>import</code>.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"c773149718f2">
<td data-local-id=3D"06a487789c34" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7df075f8f7c4"><strong>Lexical features</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"3ca8e51ed40d" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"de6ca6956449">String- and token-based features used for retr=
ieval and reranking: <code>normalized_name</code>, <code>identifier_tokens<=
/code>, <code>normalized_signature</code>, <code>normalized_body_tokens</co=
de>.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"89f15ebc5171">
<td data-local-id=3D"bb2a0bd312c1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8026768085db"><strong>Structural features</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"dcc65b4bee97" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"14374c97faf6">Non-vector program-shape features used for rer=
anking: <code>canonical_kind/language_kind</code>, <code>parameter_count</c=
ode>, <code>parent_kind</code>, <code>parent_symbol</code>, <code>path/modu=
le ancestry</code>, <code>control_shape_counts</code>, <code>callee_set_fin=
gerprint</code>.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"57a10131ab1c">
<td data-local-id=3D"6a31a93979cc" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"55be379f719f"><strong>Normalized implementation/body tokens<=
/strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"4d03a3da3446" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"1360ecd7c5f3">Tokens from the implementation body after remo=
ving formatting-only differences and other non-semantic noise under a versi=
oned normalisation policy. It has been simplified into a canonical form for=
 comparison</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"d41968a5e62c">
<td data-local-id=3D"5053b9d5fb81" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"44d36fbe06be"><strong>Provider</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"c78a458f24bc" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"56d2bbec7af3">The runtime adapter that produces summaries or=
 embeddings. A provider can call a hosted API or a local model server.</p><=
/td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"5a8218afacbc">
<td data-local-id=3D"0be0fa2fb2b5" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3f2ec9cda718"><strong>Model</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"06426b3f3f3b" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fa70ce5ef4fe">The concrete summarization or embedding model =
exposed by a provider.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"9c2a271ee443">
<td data-local-id=3D"7744de57bbac" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8010dca6b8be"><strong>exact_duplicate</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"8f795e1057ec" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c6ebeb941b83">Two artefacts have the same normalized impleme=
ntation and the same signature shape.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"bdb1049ce0c9">
<td data-local-id=3D"361fd2bb5c93" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"712d12cd6b39"><strong>similar_implementation</strong></p></t=
d>
<td data-local-id=3D"c32c6e034254" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"06933801907a">Two artefacts solve the same or very similar t=
ask but are not exact duplicates.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"39887aacfc65">
<td data-local-id=3D"77f3509111ff" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"07daaf9ca864"><strong>shared_logic_candidate</strong></p></t=
d>
<td data-local-id=3D"a15b400c1ace" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"de7912bad8a8">Two or more artefacts share repeated logic wit=
h small variation, making helper extraction a likely improvement.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"64347d52e32e">
<td data-local-id=3D"83e4cef643d3" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"12e550c9f785"><strong>diverged_implementation</strong></p></=
td>
<td data-local-id=3D"17e7e7d2067e" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6502caacc820">Two artefacts share strong lexical or ancestry=
 similarity but their implementation behaviour has drifted.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"d0a54fcee222">
<td data-local-id=3D"a6cc98b4dfee" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8dac356fc69f"><strong>weak_clone_candidate</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"e780f05e48ec" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a7aa1d9b096f">Two artefacts are worth showing in clone searc=
h, but the evidence is too weak to treat them as a strong clone match.</p><=
/td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"06628d8386d6">
<td data-local-id=3D"604f4eaba7cf" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f2da6d34f808"><strong>relation_kind</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"e7e7d48d1bd0" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c78f5b81f35c">All the above kinds:<br>
exact_duplicate, similar_implementation, shared_logic_candidate, diverged_i=
mplementation, weak_clone_candidate |</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr local-id=3D"043eb8d368f8">
<h2 local-id=3D"b4f22ce65cd7" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-5.FunctionalFlow(Mermaid)">5. Functional Flow=
 (Mermaid)</h2>
<p local-id=3D"c8490ff36959"><em>(Visual representation of system behaviour=
. Diagrams must align with BDD scenarios and contracts.)</em></p>
<h3 local-id=3D"5c307aed4241" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-5.1High-levelflow">5.1 High-level flow</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">flowcha=
rt TD
    A["Repo snapshot"] --&gt; B["Blast Radius artefacts"]
    B --&gt; C["Semantic Clones
Stage 1: summaries + features"]
    C --&gt; D["Stage 2: embeddings"]
    D --&gt; E["Stage 3: combined ranking + clone edges"]
    E --&gt; F["symbol_clone_edges"]
    E --&gt; G["clones() query stage"]
    G --&gt; H["Developer UI / Review workflow / Agent context bundle"]</pr=
e>
</div>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"1eb6ada4d8a0" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-5.2Query/ingestresponsibilitysplit">5.2 Query=
/ingest responsibility split</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">flowcha=
rt LR
    A["Blast Radius ingest"] --&gt; B["Stored summaries/features/embeddings=
/clone edges"]
    B --&gt; C["clones() runtime query"]
    C --&gt; D["Explainable results"]</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr local-id=3D"bbb7ea47f680">
<h2 local-id=3D"74a12a38bc25" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-6.Design">6. Design</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"6e819c243e9c" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-6.1Stage0dependency:BlastRadiuscontract">6.1 =
Stage 0 dependency: Blast Radius contract</h3>
<p local-id=3D"d71200647889">This feature consumes existing outputs from Bl=
ast Radius and does not re-parse code during query execution.</p>
<h4 local-id=3D"6aed6b43c9de" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-WhatSemanticClonesusesfromBlastRadius">What S=
emantic Clones uses from Blast Radius</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"aba7bef2f0ef">
<li local-id=3D"16bf1d1dd2fa">
<p local-id=3D"98e942f0d67c">parser-backed eligible artefacts</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"485353976821">
<p local-id=3D"512f42df33cd">canonical kind / language kind</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6781d4f57312">
<p local-id=3D"8f5814ac03e4">path and parent/container information</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1043b09e95ef">
<p local-id=3D"a3a1e4f9aa3a">signatures and ranges</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0e2e1d3ae246">
<p local-id=3D"45aac195799a">modifiers</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"82dfcf107447">
<p local-id=3D"d1ebd8322fc6">docstring</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3bc92cda667e">
<p local-id=3D"d6f4876ae798">call edges and dependency edges used later for=
 overlap scoring and explanations</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"30f53e433ab1" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-WhatSemanticClonesdoesnotassume">What Semanti=
c Clones does <strong>not</strong> assume</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"a57bebf0d9ac">
<li local-id=3D"3e44f7be2a36">
<p local-id=3D"773cbf8091fe">comments/docstrings are correct</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a5b6469ff519">
<p local-id=3D"a68f25c0c902">all languages are supported</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4ad945839c7f">
<p local-id=3D"b610a2f2fc86">all artefact kinds exist</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"c011f9a81a61" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-6.2Internaldesignstages">6.2 Internal design =
stages</h3>
<p local-id=3D"e6220712f92a">This feature is implemented in three internal =
stages:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"8eb9218009d6">
<li local-id=3D"b9bea056b495">
<p local-id=3D"27f615918160"><strong>Stage 1: summaries and retrieval featu=
res</strong><br>
Generates one-line summaries plus lexical and structural features.<br>
See: <a href=3D"https://bitloops.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ADCP/pages/46052=
1488/Semantic+Clones+Stage+1+-+Summaries+and+Retrieval+Features" data-linke=
d-resource-id=3D"460521488" data-linked-resource-version=3D"13" data-linked=
-resource-type=3D"page">Semantic Clones Stage 1 - Summaries and Retrieval F=
eatures</a></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"edc396ce38b1">
<p local-id=3D"36098734dc10"><strong>Stage 2: embeddings</strong><br>
Generates embeddings used for semantic similarity.<br>
See: <a href=3D"https://bitloops.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ADCP/pages/46048=
8718/Semantic+Clones+Stage+2+-+Embeddings" data-linked-resource-id=3D"46048=
8718" data-linked-resource-version=3D"16" data-linked-resource-type=3D"page=
">Semantic Clones Stage 2 - Embeddings</a></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"099d84eced67">
<p local-id=3D"3277571ba886"><strong>Stage 3: combined ranking and clone ed=
ges</strong><br>
Combines semantic, lexical, and structural signals into final scored clone =
results.<br>
See: <a href=3D"https://bitloops.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ADCP/pages/46058=
7023/Semantic+Clones+Stage+3+-+Combined+Ranking+and+Clone+Edges" data-linke=
d-resource-id=3D"460587023" data-linked-resource-version=3D"10" data-linked=
-resource-type=3D"page">Semantic Clones Stage 3 - Combined Ranking and Clon=
e Edges</a></p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"e12fb89c7e67" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-6.3Incrementalindexing">6.3 Incremental index=
ing</h3>
<p local-id=3D"7c80851646e0">Incremental indexing is a recomputation policy=
 across the entire feature.</p>
<h4 local-id=3D"a43965e52ffa" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-Rules">Rules</h4>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"6c38ef6bf332">
<li local-id=3D"975766fbd673">
<p local-id=3D"ef3a0be8bb93">Reuse existing Stage 1 output if the summary i=
nput hash is unchanged.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d777b8f45850">
<p local-id=3D"458e364c6905">Reuse existing embeddings if embedding input h=
ash is unchanged for the same provider/model.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6ab118493e5a">
<p local-id=3D"e1c3ca4bb76a">Recompute Stage 3 edges only for changed artef=
acts and their affected neighbourhood.</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"c3735ae3597f">This is how the feature stays affordable on re=
peated runs and does not have to recompute everything from the beginning wi=
th every change.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"513826c0a876">
<h2 local-id=3D"454cff893981" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-7.DataModelChanges">7. Data Model Changes</h2=
>
<p local-id=3D"d24b3353823b"><em>(Database or domain model modifications re=
quired for this feature.)</em></p>
<h3 local-id=3D"9019f74a0d4c" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-7.1Schemastatusandstoragedecision">7.1 Schema=
 status and storage decision</h3>
<p local-id=3D"8279b3cef5a4">The schema below is the <strong>final logical =
MVP contract</strong> for this capability. Physical SQL types may differ sl=
ightly between adapters, but the logical fields and meanings are fixed here=
.</p>
<p local-id=3D"6dc8b7311b90">Storage decision:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"06bc238cd0bd">
<li local-id=3D"35e053aa80f7">
<p local-id=3D"97830cd4ecd5"><strong>Hosted/shared deployment:</strong> rel=
ational store with vector support, e.g. Postgres + <code>pgvector</code></p=
></li>
<li local-id=3D"0a3f3204638d">
<p local-id=3D"4aebade8427c"><strong>Local/dev setup:</strong> local relati=
onal store with vector support, e.g. SQLite + <code>sqlite-vec</code></p></=
li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"052313fabbb1">This follows the existing DevQL relational-pro=
vider model. The capability contract remains the same across adapters.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"90beca38010c" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-7.2Tablesandtheirroles">7.2 Tables and their =
roles</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"aebbefc5f62c">
<li local-id=3D"c4ea2d19e128">
<p local-id=3D"05e9bdaed1b2"><code>symbol_semantics</code>: human-readable =
semantic description layer used in query results and context compression</p=
></li>
<li local-id=3D"5bd891c932a5">
<p local-id=3D"9508164ce2f0"><code>symbol_features</code>: deterministic le=
xical/structural signal layer used for reranking and explanations</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"fc8fbe02f3e9">
<p local-id=3D"e0ce956816ec"><code>symbol_embeddings</code>: vector-search =
layer used for nearest-neighbour retrieval</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f3a4a98fc509">
<p local-id=3D"10f8586ed87b"><code>symbol_clone_edges</code>: precomputed l=
ow-latency query layer used by <code>clones()</code> so the system does not=
 rerun the full hybrid ranking pipeline on every user request</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"dbc43b4c7730" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-7.3Outputrowcontract">7.3 Output row contract=
</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">type Se=
manticCloneRow =3D {
  relation_kind:
    | "exact_duplicate"
    | "similar_implementation"
    | "shared_logic_candidate"
    | "diverged_implementation"
    | "weak_clone_candidate";
  score: number;
  semantic_score: number;
  lexical_score: number;
  structural_score: number;
  explanation_json: object;
  source_artefact_id: string;
  source_path: string;
  source_symbol_fqn: string;
  target_artefact_id: string;
  target_path: string;
  target_symbol_fqn: string;
  target_canonical_kind: string;
  target_language: string;
  target_language_kind: string;
  target_summary?: string | null;
};</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"a9057cbd1c57">Current implementation note:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"821d70878a09">
<li local-id=3D"958aa1f86b35">
<p local-id=3D"c3f924e2f91f"><code>preferred_local_pattern</code> is not a =
dedicated top-level field today</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3c3115f27852">
<p local-id=3D"cb5a10ee05f6">when present, it appears inside <code>explanat=
ion_json.labels</code></p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"1a2665d8259d">
<h2 local-id=3D"8d81878320e6" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-8.QueryContractandCurrentDevQLclones()Capabil=
ity">8. Query Contract and Current DevQL <code>clones()</code> Capability</=
h2>
<p local-id=3D"642cd1931161"><em>(Explicit definition of the user-facing in=
terface for this capability, with a separate clarification of what the curr=
ent DevQL implementation supports as of March 18, 2026.)</em></p>
<h3 local-id=3D"b955502265fd" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-8.1StagenameusedinDevQLtoday">8.1 Stage name =
used in DevQL today</h3>
<p local-id=3D"1d7eee71fa45">The implemented DevQL stage name is <code>clon=
es()</code>.</p>
<p local-id=3D"6b1a2709bcbf">Throughout this page, =E2=80=9Csemantic clone =
retrieval=E2=80=9D describes the capability. In actual DevQL syntax today, =
the query stage name is <code>clones()</code>.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"55ac4bc36b76" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-8.2Whatclones()does">8.2 What <code>clones()<=
/code> does</h3>
<p local-id=3D"5cdd1ce4569e"><code>clones()</code> reads clone matches for =
the currently selected artefact set and returns rows from the clone-edge la=
yer.</p>
<p local-id=3D"33f8e37928f6">In simple terms:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"f235f877d6e4">
<li local-id=3D"0614d97577c9">
<p local-id=3D"4d9c72318f4f">the stages before <code>clones()</code> decide=
 <strong>which artefacts are the source side</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"32a4df5d22cb">
<p local-id=3D"88df93dd6b46"><code>clones()</code> looks up clone matches f=
or those source artefacts</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3470d545a1fe">
<p local-id=3D"46e6de4fb6d3"><code>clones()</code> can then filter those ma=
tches by relation kind and minimum score</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"43d66195f43a">
<p local-id=3D"3e306abbf141">downstream stages such as <code>limit()</code>=
 reduce the returned result set further</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"ecc59e72b528"><code>clones()</code> does <strong>not</strong=
> discover a source artefact on its own. It depends on a prior <code>artefa=
cts()</code> stage.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"d3881b80e4b8" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-8.3Directargumentssupportedtoday">8.3 Direct =
arguments supported today</h3>
<p local-id=3D"6b3ee2e43b6c">The parser supports only these direct <code>cl=
ones()</code> arguments:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"2f=
6ae335bcce" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"d4efdec98a22">
<th data-local-id=3D"bc57c29f84ca" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"6784ceaf8a57">Argument</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"a4a6c3480b1c" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"7e81349b7824">Type</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"3ab8481fcaf4" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"646f3d83281a">Meaning</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"53792bc558ba">
<td data-local-id=3D"bd73b094b70f" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"57fe7be01a50"><code>relation_kind</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"d628598934e1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"27206c6d8a38"><code>string</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"e37ff38b9d9e" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b0efa5ae20d5">Keep only clone rows with the given clone clas=
s</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"321244f98c8b">
<td data-local-id=3D"cde6650254ab" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4a0481f6f816"><code>min_score</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"bfdcd1a2b006" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0d17865a3552"><code>float 0.0..1.0</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"dc414bee8e6d" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"94364300baff">Keep only clone rows whose final score is grea=
ter than or equal to the given threshold</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"92a821305bc4">These are applied as filters over clone-edge r=
ows:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"56a17781fe74">
<li local-id=3D"0aaefbf71201">
<p local-id=3D"75bd205b8b0c"><code>relation_kind</code> filters <code>ce.re=
lation_kind =3D ...</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"71b3c990a866">
<p local-id=3D"485e972908bd"><code>min_score</code> filters <code>ce.score =
&gt;=3D ...</code></p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"a077d16cd263" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-8.4Relationkindssupportedbyclones()today">8.4=
 Relation kinds supported by <code>clones()</code> today</h3>
<p local-id=3D"3b1f47a7463e">The current implementation supports the <code>=
relation_kind</code> we have mentioned above.<br>
Important clarification:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"a93ddf860361">
<li local-id=3D"823c2cc93846">
<p local-id=3D"f70eafb27b80"><code>preferred_local_pattern</code> is <stron=
g>not</strong> a <code>relation_kind</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9829d5ebacc0">
<p local-id=3D"c66a77d4ed0d">it is only a secondary label inside <code>expl=
anation_json</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7350cf513e43">
<p local-id=3D"c32416a723a7">therefore it cannot be queried with <code>rela=
tion_kind:"preferred_local_pattern"</code></p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"363a2589ac02" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-8.5Howthesourcesideisselectedbeforeclones()">=
8.5 How the source side is selected before <code>clones()</code></h3>
<p local-id=3D"bfcfc7a1841b"><code>clones()</code> operates on the artefact=
s selected earlier in the query.</p>
<p local-id=3D"26492df155dd">The common source-shaping patterns are:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"8dd81fcfb64c">
<li local-id=3D"78ca7ebe1009">
<p local-id=3D"419c0f645853"><code>artefacts(kind:"...")</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1ea725aafaba">
<p local-id=3D"68f9fb49a1fe"><code>artefacts(symbol_fqn:"...")</code></p></=
li>
<li local-id=3D"c204c8de427b">
<p local-id=3D"ee08f27aa7c1"><code>artefacts(lines:"...")</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"af39a31dd988">
<p local-id=3D"2027121c33e7"><code>file("...") -&gt; artefacts(...)</code><=
/p></li>
<li local-id=3D"37f545ec97fd">
<p local-id=3D"513130edf61d"><code>files(path:"...") -&gt; artefacts(...)</=
code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b55631562b24">
<p local-id=3D"6755f1825504"><code>artefacts(agent:"...", since:"...")</cod=
e></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"5de701a3937f">The important rule is:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"bc11471ffe88">
<li local-id=3D"fd87e25d1c13">
<p local-id=3D"2224aa17a5be"><code>clones()</code> requires an <code>artefa=
cts()</code> stage</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"4df9d3c2d0a6">So <code>file()</code> and <code>files()</code=
> can narrow the search space before clone lookup, but clone lookup still h=
appens over the artefacts selected by <code>artefacts()</code>.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"ff89a23967bf" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-8.6Validqueryexamples">8.6 Valid query exampl=
es</h3>
<p local-id=3D"68516ab1f2f1">The following query shapes are valid with the =
current implementation:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">repo("x=
")-&gt;artefacts(symbol_fqn:"...")-&gt;clones()</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">repo("x=
")-&gt;artefacts(symbol_fqn:"...")-&gt;clones(min_score:0.7)</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">repo("x=
")-&gt;artefacts(symbol_fqn:"...")-&gt;clones(relation_kind:"exact_duplicat=
e")</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">repo("x=
")-&gt;artefacts(kind:"method")-&gt;clones(relation_kind:"shared_logic_cand=
idate", min_score:0.6)-&gt;limit(10)</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"95a204d3e02a" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-8.7Currentrestrictions">8.7 Current restricti=
ons</h3>
<p local-id=3D"52d4d6a656f8">The current implementation has these restricti=
ons:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"3ac6ed56c142">
<li local-id=3D"ba0682863697">
<p local-id=3D"2fbbab453378"><code>clones()</code> requires an <code>artefa=
cts()</code> stage</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c71247ceca49">
<p local-id=3D"7d62751e8fac"><code>clones()</code> cannot be combined with =
<code>deps()</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0230aa02c1e1">
<p local-id=3D"04330a31addc"><code>clones()</code> cannot be combined with =
<code>chatHistory()</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a0285294a35f">
<p local-id=3D"26608530efc1"><code>clones()</code> does not support <code>a=
sOf(...)</code></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"4eca86086d40">These restrictions should be read as <strong>c=
urrent implementation limits</strong>, not as permanent product goals.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"83b63aeb6537">
<h2 local-id=3D"1f20b1d9d558" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-9.BusinessRules">9. Business Rules</h2>
<p local-id=3D"b9bd66e077a3"><em>(Deterministic logic that governs system b=
ehaviour. Must be explicit and exhaustive.)</em></p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"afbc324f5140">
<li local-id=3D"2b68b2379671">
<p local-id=3D"d2fd6acb0823">Semantic Clones operates only on supported lan=
guages: TypeScript, JavaScript, and Rust.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"410cb374a9b6">
<p local-id=3D"cff1e2224a2b">Semantic Clones operates only within a single =
repository snapshot.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"826986b80838">
<p local-id=3D"546b14b04b15">Blast Radius output is the structural source o=
f truth for artefact identity and shape.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"70eb5c2e06b0">
<p local-id=3D"d9fd11bdb259">Comments/docstrings are supporting evidence on=
ly and must never override implementation-derived structure.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9e5c9332cf7c">
<p local-id=3D"79be9091fc73">Every eligible artefact gets a final one-line =
summary, even when model inference is disabled.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"46343e6317c3">
<p local-id=3D"59eb66e9c51d">Exact duplicate classification is deterministi=
c and does not rely on embeddings.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"48c967a61ff0">
<p local-id=3D"292ddfaf8371">Similarity scores are only comparable inside t=
he same provider/model/dimension/input-version space.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d721be3a75fb">
<p local-id=3D"b60c7e828156">Every returned clone row must include <code>re=
lation_kind</code>, <code>score</code>, <code>semantic_score</code>, <code>=
lexical_score</code>, <code>structural_score</code>, and <code>explanation_=
json</code>.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c5e112ed4b64">
<p local-id=3D"fdbb84d36ad8"><code>preferred_local_pattern</code> is a rank=
ing label, not a separate relation kind.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f059fce16f53">
<p local-id=3D"1acb058c3e74">MVP weights are fixed defaults and are not que=
ry-level user configuration.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ad44b799a526">
<p local-id=3D"703422489c99">If embedding configuration is missing or inval=
id, Stage 2 fails clearly and writes no partial embedding rows for that run=
.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"93ce337603f7">
<p local-id=3D"75347afe5724">Blast Radius call edges and dependency edges m=
ay contribute to Stage 3 scoring and explanation payloads.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5638101b3a27">
<p local-id=3D"41247a6267bc"><code>weak_clone_candidate</code> is used when=
 a result is worth surfacing but the evidence is still too weak for a stron=
ger clone class.</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"5e889afcd80f">No hidden logic outside this section.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"aee18977aebd">
<h2 local-id=3D"f008eaee7348" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-10.UserStories">10. User Stories</h2>
<p local-id=3D"fa7b357534e7"><em>(High-level narrative groupings of user in=
tent. Used for understanding context, not implementation tracking.)</em></p=
>
<p local-id=3D"db62a2c82516">These stories are grouped by <strong>capabilit=
y outcomes returned from the same public query stage</strong>, not by separ=
ate public APIs.</p>
<p local-id=3D"cea2b000cab4"><strong>US1 - Find similar implementations by =
intent</strong><br>
As a developer, reviewer, or AI agent<br>
I want to retrieve local functions, methods, or modules that solve a simila=
r problem even when names differ<br>
So that I can reuse local patterns instead of writing bespoke implementatio=
ns</p>
<p local-id=3D"4c9082246c94"><strong>US2 - Detect exact duplicates and extr=
action candidates</strong><br>
As a developer, reviewer, or AI agent<br>
I want Bitloops to highlight exact duplicates and highly similar repeated l=
ogic<br>
So that I can consolidate repeated code, extract a helper, or avoid reimple=
menting an existing solution</p>
<p local-id=3D"ab67d93e803a"><strong>US3 - Detect divergent forks</strong><=
br>
As a developer or reviewer<br>
I want to see when related implementations have drifted apart<br>
So that I can review whether the divergence is intentional or risky</p>
<p local-id=3D"4725689fb55f"><strong>US4 - Surface weak clone candidates wi=
thout overstating confidence</strong><br>
As a developer or reviewer<br>
I want Bitloops to show nearby implementations that may still be useful to =
inspect<br>
So that I can review them without confusing them with strong clone matches<=
/p>
<p local-id=3D"61e63eccc0e1"><strong>US5 - Prefer strong local patterns</st=
rong><br>
As an AI agent<br>
I want clone results to surface the strongest local example first<br>
So that generated changes follow repository conventions</p>
<p local-id=3D"39ee9cd76b00"><strong>US6 - Understand why a match was retur=
ned</strong><br>
As a developer or reviewer<br>
I want every result to include component scores and explanation evidence<br=
>
So that I can trust or reject it quickly</p>
<p local-id=3D"2d9e0d4c2180"><strong>US7 - Keep enrichment incremental and =
affordable</strong><br>
As a platform engineer<br>
I want recomputation to affect only changed artefacts and their neighbourho=
od<br>
So that repeated indexing remains practical</p>
<hr local-id=3D"80103c7bf3ea">
<h2 local-id=3D"c7b8a433fad6" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-11.BDDScenarios(SourceofTruth)">11. BDD Scena=
rios (Source of Truth)</h2>
<p local-id=3D"728441173e96"><em>(Executable requirements. Every scenario h=
as an ID and maps directly to acceptance criteria.)</em></p>
<p local-id=3D"7d23e6b7a694">These scenarios map to either the public retri=
eval stage <code>clones()</code> or the enrichment workflow <code>semanticC=
loneEnrich</code>.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"9bff7372e43d" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-11.1clones()happypaths">11.1 <code>clones()</=
code> happy paths</h3>
<p local-id=3D"078bbf038f9e"><strong>S1 - Similar implementations are retri=
eved even when names differ</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given t=
wo artefacts in the same repository snapshot that implement the same busine=
ss intent
And their identifiers are not lexically identical
And summaries, features, and embeddings exist for both
When clones() runs for one artefact
Then the other artefact is returned as a clone candidate
And the result includes relation_kind, score, component scores, and explana=
tion payload</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"d9d77cd5c6d9"><strong>S2 - Exact duplicates are classified s=
eparately</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given t=
wo artefacts whose normalized AST hash and normalized body hash are equal
When clones() runs
Then the other artefact is returned with relation_kind exact_duplicate
And deterministic hash equality is sufficient for classification
And signature shape is not required for that label</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"c669b60f8b05"><strong>S3 - Extraction candidates are surface=
d deterministically</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given t=
wo artefacts where exact_duplicate is false
And repeated_logic_overlap is at least 0.35
And lexical_score is at least 0.55
And structural_score is at least 0.50
When clones() runs
Then the pair can be labeled extraction_candidate
And the explanation identifies the repeated logic signal</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"1798b739411f"><strong>S4 - Divergent forks are identified an=
d explained deterministically</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given t=
wo artefacts where exact_duplicate is false
And ancestry_score is at least 0.70
And lexical_score is at least 0.70
And semantic_score is at least 0.45 and below 0.75
And structural_score is at most 0.50
When clones() runs
Then the pair is labeled divergent_fork
And the explanation states that ancestry is similar while implementation be=
haviour has drifted</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"e1557c361f77"><strong>S5 - Preferred local patterns are rank=
ed ahead of weaker neighbours</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given m=
ultiple similar implementations for a target artefact
And candidate A has score at least 0.80
And candidate A has commits_touching_path_last_90d less than or equal to 2
And candidate A is reachable from the default branch
And candidate A is not an exact duplicate
When clones() ranks the results
Then candidate A may be labeled preferred_local_pattern
And candidate A appears ahead of otherwise weaker matches</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"52a9e385f333"><strong>S6 - Weak clone candidates are surface=
d but clearly labeled</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given t=
wo artefacts in the same repository snapshot
And candidate_score is at least 0.55
And semantic_score is at least 0.55
And locality dominates implementation evidence
When clones() runs
Then the pair is returned with relation_kind weak_clone_candidate
And the explanation includes locality bias evidence
And the result is not treated as a preferred local pattern</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"669a6631c09b" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-11.2Edgecases">11.2 Edge cases</h3>
<p local-id=3D"17b2ec1802aa"><strong>E1 - Every eligible artefact gets a su=
mmary</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
n eligible artefact in a supported language
When Stage 1 runs
Then a template summary is always produced
And if a valid detail clause is available it is appended
And otherwise the template summary alone is stored</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"8995f16976d0"><strong>E2 - Comments do not override implemen=
tation truth</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
n artefact whose docstring or leading comment is stale
When Stage 1 runs
Then the final summary still reflects implementation-derived structure
And the stale comment does not override the generated summary</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"ad729d07437e"><strong>E3 - Incremental indexing reuses uncha=
nged work</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 new repository snapshot where only one eligible artefact changed
And unchanged artefacts still have the same summary and embedding input has=
hes
When Stage1 runs
Then unchanged artefacts reuse their existing summaries and embeddings
And clone edges are recomputed only for the changed artefact and its affect=
ed neighbourhood</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"788115e44c93" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-11.3Errorcases">11.3 Error cases</h3>
<p local-id=3D"18ae77fefd2e"><strong>ERR1 - Missing embedding configuration=
 fails clearly</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given s=
emanticCloneEnrich is requested without a valid embedding provider configur=
ation
When Stage 2 starts
Then the system returns a clear actionable configuration error
And no partial embedding rows are written for that run</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr local-id=3D"5c2a65402209">
<h2 local-id=3D"ed0d45c2ecc2" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-12.AcceptanceCriteria">12. Acceptance Criteri=
a</h2>
<p local-id=3D"ca14bb320b0c"><em>(Testable conditions that must be satisfie=
d for the feature to be considered complete. Directly derived from BDD scen=
ario IDs.)</em></p>
<ul local-id=3D"c04c79e3f5a1">
<li local-id=3D"1aed40d41191">
<p local-id=3D"5477f7dddbcf">S1 must return semantically similar artefacts =
even when names differ, with relation kind, overall score, component scores=
, and explanation payload.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"48f0ae2a9b47">
<p local-id=3D"04d225367c46">S2 must classify exact duplicates through dete=
rministic normalised-hash rules rather than embeddings alone.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5148b68695dc">
<p local-id=3D"61c9c481bd94">S3 must surface extraction candidates when rep=
eated logic overlap and the required lexical/structural thresholds are met.=
</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8b162a5f65b7">
<p local-id=3D"3f84873e9fd1">S4 must classify divergent forks when the defi=
ned ancestry, lexical, semantic, and structural thresholds are met.</p></li=
>
<li local-id=3D"332e0e48010c">
<p local-id=3D"8bf56ce9a9b1">S5 must allow strong local examples to be rank=
ed above weaker neighbours and labeled as preferred local patterns when the=
 defined score and churn criteria are met.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1bd5514746b8">
<p local-id=3D"5461d14d1255">S6 must surface weak clone candidates with an =
explicit weak label and locality-bias explanation instead of presenting the=
m as strong clone matches.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c6ba793303f2">
<p local-id=3D"1b88be32c94c">E1 must produce a final summary for every elig=
ible artefact by always generating a template summary and optionally append=
ing a validated detail clause.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0a1371becd2e">
<p local-id=3D"bf0479c650ea">E2 must treat comments/docstrings as supportin=
g evidence only and must not allow stale comments to override implementatio=
n-derived structure.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b0aeb8873fc1">
<p local-id=3D"2349c567d085">E3 must skip unnecessary recomputation for unc=
hanged artefacts and only refresh clone edges for changed artefacts and the=
ir affected neighbourhood.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"10bf9163bf05">
<p local-id=3D"d2fc2944374e">ERR1 must fail with actionable feedback when e=
mbeddings cannot be generated because provider configuration is missing or =
invalid.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7744d0553b4b">
<p local-id=3D"8f7100259f66">Every returned clone row must include <code>re=
lation_kind</code>, <code>score</code>, <code>semantic_score</code>, <code>=
lexical_score</code>, <code>structural_score</code>, and <code>explanation_=
json</code>, and any <code>preferred_local_pattern</code> label must appear=
 inside <code>explanation_json.labels</code>.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"b2c430a51871">
<h2 local-id=3D"d25e2bf0ba06" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-13.Dependencies">13. Dependencies</h2>
<p local-id=3D"14ca7979fed1"><em>(Internal or external systems, services, o=
r teams required for delivery.)</em></p>
<ul local-id=3D"4bca5443314b">
<li local-id=3D"97e94bf9c8a5">
<p local-id=3D"88394de1e849">Blast Radius V1 artefact extraction and depend=
ency edges</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8a06847aadab">
<p local-id=3D"55735e3c4fd2">DevQL plugin registry and query-stage registra=
tion</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"68032f724d52">
<h2 local-id=3D"10a98933585b" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-14.DefinitionofDone">14. Definition of Done</=
h2>
<p local-id=3D"e94f1fb3f1ad">Feature is Done when:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"c5af6db19135">
<li local-id=3D"c95151e0399d">
<p local-id=3D"b10b72069823">all BDD scenarios pass</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a71db9c259d0">
<p local-id=3D"6ba5eaf1d69e">acceptance criteria are met</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a8c9e8799518">
<p local-id=3D"bb36543a29ff">plugin-boundary tests and integration tests pa=
ss</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"17cbc4136214">
<p local-id=3D"a72b5a0398ca">documentation is updated</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b82ed4e47d91">
<p local-id=3D"40770da92c33">no blocking open questions remain</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"53b3de798059" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-15.NextSteps">15. Next Steps</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"1aef24f89de7" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-15.1ImplementBDDcoverage">15.1 Implement BDD =
coverage</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"7d982670a4c7">
<li local-id=3D"7219f11683f9">
<p local-id=3D"e495a43a8d7a">Implement the BDD scenarios already listed in =
this spec.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"be8397de6ae8">
<p local-id=3D"e388ca2c94bb">Start with <code>clones()</code> happy paths a=
nd the Stage 1 summary fallback cases.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"0824a8e06d19" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-15.2RefactorSemanticClonesintoacapabilitypack=
">15.2 Refactor Semantic Clones into a capability pack</h3>
<p local-id=3D"457c76494369">The current code is already split into the thr=
ee main modules below, which makes this refactor mostly an orchestration ch=
ange rather than a logic rewrite:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"8ba2eb72b18d">
<li local-id=3D"574710a8eefc">
<p local-id=3D"5d662b16cfcf"><code>bitloops_cli/src/engine/semantic_clones<=
/code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"25262be6e312">
<p local-id=3D"04154efab7c7"><code>bitloops_cli/src/engine/semantic_embeddi=
ngs</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ae9f71ee3130">
<p local-id=3D"e941a89b251a"><code>bitloops_cli/src/engine/semantic_feature=
s</code></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"57c544b69e8b">The strongest remaining coupling is in DevQL i=
ngest and init.</p>
<p local-id=3D"81977bacfc11">The refactor goal is:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"8b493114bc5a">
<li local-id=3D"b22d034e059b">
<p local-id=3D"a46615e788b4">keep the Semantic Clones logic modular</p></li=
>
<li local-id=3D"c60818a15934">
<p local-id=3D"5bbbec6fd2d2">make capability execution pluggable through th=
e capability-pack architecture</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e0a77543ddc6">
<p local-id=3D"aa6bb0374a3b">avoid unnecessary database changes while doing=
 that refactor</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"ef11ec51e202">For now, the database design does not need to =
change. The existing tables are already queryable and mutable, so this step=
 is mainly about execution boundaries and registration.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"51d2ef7b75c9" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RevisedFeatureSpec-15.3Evaluateclonequalityusingmultiplesourcear=
tefacts">15.3 Evaluate clone quality using multiple source artefacts</h3>
<p local-id=3D"6e64dc88baab">The current example is useful, but it mostly t=
ests same-file neighbours. The test is from the <code>bitloops-platform</co=
de> repo with changes in a command handler:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">bitloop=
s devql query 'repo("bitloops-platform")-&gt;artefacts(kind:"method",symbol=
_fqn:"d2c-backend/src/bounded-contexts/d2c/code-implementation/application/=
command-handlers/create-component-snapshots.handler.ts::CreateComponentSnap=
shotsCommandHandler::execute")-&gt;clones()-&gt;limit(100)'</pre>
</div>
</div>
