<p local-id=3D"0abc9aafa924">What the current output is telling us:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"5ec75ec58cdb">
<li local-id=3D"2682d7109a41">
<p local-id=3D"0fbb55a4e626">the top matches are <code>weak_clone_candidate=
</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"46e22a5a3aa1">
<p local-id=3D"81fe8f56580d">the top matches come from the same file and sa=
me container</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8b7da54b31a1">
<p local-id=3D"c9bf42800ca6">the explanation payload includes <code>same_fi=
le_bias</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d9521597b6c2">
<p local-id=3D"5b6ef8932e4b">clone confidence is low, so these are weak nei=
ghbours rather than strong reusable matches</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"cdae3bd1bac9">A compact reading of the sample output is:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"91=
96718a3a9d" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"730041b27fea">
<th data-local-id=3D"c8e9b50e58f3" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"363fcb62c8e2">Signal</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"d96b27591754" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"aef908e0d3d8">What it means</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"1d7c3265ab7f">
<td data-local-id=3D"ba87f68a1876" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"702157c73460"><code>relation_kind =3D weak_clone_candidate</=
code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"722f0c7abe2d" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"35476df53053">show the result, but do not treat it as a stro=
ng clone match</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"b9b25e4c4e06">
<td data-local-id=3D"2bd25a55d43f" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a1f89a0b4ebb"><code>same_file_bias</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"26974140e893" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f819a416e16e">locality is helping the score a lot because so=
urce and target are very close in the codebase</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"f72748a7cb40">
<td data-local-id=3D"d4cb5a72a966" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"98f39451a3c2"><code>low_call_overlap</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"eff9ee2d6810" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"462e361f21b3">the called operations do not overlap enough to=
 support a stronger match</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"ddcc602159cf">
<td data-local-id=3D"04031da83bca" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"eef4e1b1be2a"><code>summary_gap</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"62a6ab904900" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b1975a3a7cf4">the summaries do not align strongly enough</p>=
</td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"fe9b9f4365af">
<td data-local-id=3D"fee8fdfb8e7f" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"358c5978f1ad"><code>clone_confidence =E2=89=88 0.32</code></=
p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"44f52bed0a74" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a7e5f4b4c5f0">useful as a weak neighbour, not yet convincing=
 as a strong implementation match</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"5d724b5853e0">This is a good calibration case, but it is not=
 enough to validate cross-handler retrieval quality because <code>execute</=
code> is a common method name and the current top matches stay inside the s=
ame file.</p>
<p local-id=3D"73682a5e6568">Suggested follow-up queries:</p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"769dd4d21009">
<li local-id=3D"8765f6e6573f">
<p local-id=3D"7b548cdd3d3b">Keep the same source method, but filter for st=
ronger results only:</p></li>
</ol>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">bitloop=
s devql query 'repo("bitloops-platform")-&gt;artefacts(kind:"method",symbol=
_fqn:"d2c-backend/src/bounded-contexts/d2c/code-implementation/application/=
command-handlers/create-component-snapshots.handler.ts::CreateComponentSnap=
shotsCommandHandler::execute")-&gt;clones(min_score:0.60)-&gt;limit(20)'</p=
re>
</div>
</div>
<ol start=3D"2" local-id=3D"2fd84076155b">
<li local-id=3D"edb00b12bf4c">
<p local-id=3D"4c9ed061c54a">Keep the same source method, but ask only for =
stronger clone classes:</p></li>
</ol>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">bitloop=
s devql query 'repo("bitloops-platform")-&gt;artefacts(kind:"method",symbol=
_fqn:"d2c-backend/src/bounded-contexts/d2c/code-implementation/application/=
command-handlers/create-component-snapshots.handler.ts::CreateComponentSnap=
shotsCommandHandler::execute")-&gt;clones(relation_kind:"similar_implementa=
tion",min_score:0.60)-&gt;limit(20)'</pre>
</div>
</div>
<ol start=3D"3" local-id=3D"2ced690e2360">
<li local-id=3D"2d302516a842">
<p local-id=3D"71967d9c8648">Repeat the same query shape for a second comma=
nd handler <code>execute</code> method in another file, and compare whether=
 the strongest results are still dominated by same-file neighbours:</p></li=
>
</ol>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">bitloop=
s devql query 'repo("bitloops-platform")-&gt;artefacts(kind:"method",symbol=
_fqn:"&lt;another-command-handler-path&gt;::&lt;AnotherCommandHandler&gt;::=
execute")-&gt;clones(min_score:0.60)-&gt;limit(20)'</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"fbe036cd4102">The goal of this follow-up is to confirm that =
clone retrieval stays useful when the source method name is generic and the=
 best results should come from other handlers, not only from helper methods=
 in the same file.</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
